    • openedPace

      public static Pace openedPace
      The currently opened Pace. Only one Pace is opened at a time. Used as a reference for any code reading or modifying the pace's state.

    • appStage

      private static javafx.stage.Stage appStage
      The currently opened stage displaying the main application. If the application is closed back to the launcher, this value is overwritten.

    • updateList

      private static List<Updatable> updateList
      List of updatable objects. Master list of all objects in the queue for updating. Each time the application updates, the Updatable.update() method is called from each object in this list.
      See Also:
      • update()

    • open

      public static void open(File file)
      Attempts to open a pace from a specified file path. First checks that the file is not null and exists. If the file is invalid, then will open a new pace file. Note that the new pace file will not have a correlating file, and will not attempt to save to the attempted file location.
      Parameters:
      file - Pace File to attempt to open. File extension does not matter.

    • createTab

      private static javafx.scene.control.Tab createTab(javafx.scene.Node node, String name)

      Creates a new tab element, configures it, and returns the tab

      Modifications:

      • Sets Closable to false
      • Sets the content to the provided node
      • Sets the title of the tab to the provided name

      Parameters:
      node - Content of the pane. Content will be displayed in the tab-pane when the tab is selected and opened
      name - Name/Title of the tab. Text is displayed on the tab itself.
      Returns:
      Configured Tab object

    • removeUpdatable

      public static boolean removeUpdatable(Updatable updatable)
      Removes an updatable from the update list. The object will no longer be pinged any time the application is updated
      Parameters:
      updatable - Updatable object that implements the Updatable interface
      Returns:
      true if this list contained the specified element
